# fedora-mirrors.list — Fedora infrastructure domain list for CIDR resolution
#
# Format: one domain per line, comments with #
# Used by: egress/allowlists/update-cidrs.sh (Phase 2 tooling)
# Purpose: resolve these domains to CIDRs → populate hisnos-updates.nft
#
# These domains represent the outbound destinations for:
#   - rpm-ostree system updates (Fedora Kinoite base image)
#   - Fedora package downloads (in toolbox/distrobox)
#   - Bodhi update notifications
#   - Koji build artifacts
#
# Refresh cadence: monthly, or when rpm-ostree update fails with connection errors
# Refresh command: sudo egress/allowlists/update-cidrs.sh --target fedora
#
# Known CDN: Fastly (151.101.0.0/16) — stable, used as primary static CIDR
# Known infrastructure: Red Hat / IBM (209.132.0.0/16) — stable

# Primary download mirrors
dl.fedoraproject.org
mirrors.fedoraproject.org
download.fedoraproject.org

# Fedora project infrastructure
src.fedoraproject.org
koji.fedoraproject.org
bodhi.fedoraproject.org
packager.fedoraproject.org
pagure.io
release-monitoring.org

# Fedora Container Registry (used by Kinoite base image pulls)
registry.fedoraproject.org
quay.io

# Red Hat Customer Portal (subscription content, if applicable)
cdn.redhat.com
subscription.rhsm.redhat.com

# Fedora Copr (third-party builds, e.g. upstream Mesa, GameMode)
copr.fedorainfracloud.org
download.copr.fedorainfracloud.org
